  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0da7 \u0db4\u0db1\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0daf\u0dd6 10 \u0d9a\u0dca \u0dad\u0dbd\u0dd9\u0db8\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dda\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "10 people who tried to jump the country are caught in Talemannar",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Navy said that 10 people suspected of trying to illegally migrate from Sri Lanka to a foreign country by sea were arrested in the sea area off the Kurusapadu area of \u200b\u200bTalemannar.",
        "During a special search operation last night (16), the P175 Coastal Patrol Vessel belonging to the Sri Lanka Naval Ship Buwaneka of the North Central Naval Command observed and inspected this suspicious dinghy and there it was said that the dinghy was trying to migrate illegally from Sri Lanka to a foreign country by sea. The Navy said the dinghy was taken into custody by the Navy along with the two operators, four males above the age of 18, two females and four below the age of 18.",
        "The Navy stated that the persons taken into the custody of the Navy were identified as residents of Pesale, Urumale, Kilinochchi and Kantale and the persons were handed over to the Thalemannar Police for further legal proceedings."
      ],
